BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313714284@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260310T023716Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260313T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260313T110000
SUMMARY:Let's Walk!! Brookdale Park
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nIf entering from Bellevue Avenue and park in the
  first parking lot on the left. We will be gathering near the the playgrou
 nd area.\n\nif entering from Watchung Ave\, park and walk up to the upper 
 parking lot near the playground area.\n\nWe will be walking the outer path
 . There are several break-off points if you do not want to walk the entire
  path.\n\nThe walk will be about an hour or at least 3-4 miles.\n\nWear co
 mfortable shoes!\n\nPlease plan to arrive 5 minutes early. The walk will s
 tart promptly.\n\nBrookdale Park offers the public access to both passive 
 and active recreational activities as well as picturesque vistas. Trails f
 or walking and running\, lush groves and extensive lawns\, playgrounds\, s
 ports fields\, track facilities\, tennis courts\, an archery range and sta
 dium grandstand are just some of the numerous attractions that make Brookd
 ale Park a magnet for nature lovers\, families\, and physical fitness enth
 usiasts for miles around.\n\nhttps://www.essexcountyparks.org/parks/brookd
 ale-park\n\nDisclaimer: If you join us for a hike\, please understand that
  you are responsible for your own preparedness and well-being and will hol
 d no one else liable in case of injury or mishap.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/313714284/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260309T165049Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260309T165049Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313688301@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260310T023716Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260314T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260314T120000
SUMMARY:Let's Walk!! Orange Reservoir Loop
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nJoin me for a loop or two around the reservoir. 
 Each loop is 1.75 miles. We will Meet at the Pavilion.\n\nThere is parking
  across the street from the Pavilion.\n\nRain or extreme weather will canc
 el the event\n\nRain date 3/15\nCollaborative walk with "Montclair Women O
 ver 50."\n\nDisclaimer: If you join us for a hike\, please understand that
  you are responsible for your own preparedness and well-being and will hol
 d no one else liable in case of injury or mishap.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/313688301/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260308T005937Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260308T005937Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313394383@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260310T023716Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T091500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T101500
SUMMARY:Eagle Rock Reservation
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nJOIN US FOR A WALK. WE WALK AT A MODERATE PACE O
 N UNPAVED PATHS.\n\nWe will hike for about an hour - 3.5 miles. We will be
  walking on trails in the woods\, so appropriate footwear\, long pants & s
 ocks\, and bug spray.\n\nWill will meet at:\n[https://goo.gl/maps/7rRRTiXC
 ntdE1neD7](https://goo.gl/maps/7rRRTiXCntdE1neD7) Eagle Rock Trail Parking
  Lot by Kiosk#1\n\nIf you enter from Eagle Rock Way\, go pass the Highlawn
  and stay left. There will be a parking lot at the end of the curve to you
 r right.\n\nEagle Rock Reservation is 408 acres of hills\, streams\, and v
 alleys located on the borders of West Orange\, Verona\, and Montclair\, Ne
 w Jersey. Though located in the middle of the most densely populated count
 y in the most densely populated state in the country\, the Reservation is 
 mostly undeveloped and boasts an extensive trail system within its borders
 .\n\n**Please make sure to RSVP and arrive 5 minutes prior to start time.*
 *\n\nFOLLOW US ON INSTAGRAM - letswalkmeetup\n\nDisclaimer: If you join us
  for a hike\, please understand that you are responsible for your own prep
 aredness and well-being and will hold no one else liable in case of injury
  or mishap. Event will be canceled in the event of extreme weather.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/313394383/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260217T063231Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260217T063231Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313099522@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260310T023716Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T110000
SUMMARY:Let's Walk!! in Belleville Park
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nLet’s get out and enjoy nature by walking abou
 t 3 miles in Belleville Park.\n\nWe will also check out the nearby Essex H
 udson Greenway and Branch Brook Park. Wear comfortable shoes and bring som
 e water!\n\nBelleville Park is a mid-sized\, 32.70-acre park designed by t
 he Olmsteds with a playground\, bocce courts\, ball fields & a jogging pat
 h. It is bordered by Belleville and Parkside Avenues and Mill Street along
  the Second River\, which was once a part of the Morris Canal.\n\n**We sta
 rt promptly\, so please arrive at least 5 minutes before the start.**\nRai
 n or extreme weather will cancel the event.\n\nDisclaimer: If you join us 
 for a hike/walk\, please understand that you are responsible for your own 
 preparedness and well-being and will hold no one else liable in case of in
 jury or mishap.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/313099522/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260128T193105Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260128T193105Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
